<subSubSection id="C30BE2BD2277FFCBFF36247BFDCCFD6C" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BAEB1362277FFCBFF36247BFC06FE1C" blockId="23.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="B9656D242277FFCBFF36247BFE95FE61" bold="true" box="[199,322,366,392]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Bright black integument, and ferruginous tarsus. Body densely covered with yellowish setae, with uneven clusters of dark setae, forming small macula scattered over the elytra, and a larger velvelty black macula in the middle of interstria 4; pronotum with oblique granules on the sides and moderately transverse on the pronotal disc, elytra with transverse granules, more concentrated in the basal third.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAEB1362277FFCBFF3624EBFE1CFD88" blockId="23.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="B9656D242277FFCBFF3624EBFDD0FDF1" bold="true" box="[199,519,510,536]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Geographical distribution.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="3B79BB6B2277FFCBFDE024EAFCB2FDD7" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3034615644" country="Peru" location="We" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" specimenCount="1">
<location id="8ECEE7ED2277FFCBFDE024EAFDE1FDF0" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B800202276FFC4FF6623F2FD38FF3C:8ECEE7ED2277FFCBFDE024EAFDE1FDF0" box="[529,566,511,537]" country="Peru" name="We" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">We</location>
did not examine any specimens of this species. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF80CCC72277FFCBFB9924EAFA4BFDF3" author="Wibmer, G. J. &amp; O'Brien, C. W." box="[1128,1436,511,538]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" pagination="1 - 563" refId="ref30526" refString="Wibmer, G. J. &amp; O'Brien, C. W. (1986) Annotated checklist of the weevils (Curculionidae sensu lato) of South America (Coleoptera: Curculionoidea). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 39, 1 - 563." type="journal article" year="1986">Wibmer &amp; O’Brien (1986)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that this species occurs only in 
<collectingCountry id="F306F1A62277FFCBFD752736FD60FDD4" box="[644,695,547,573]" name="Peru" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<typeStatus id="54AA0F942277FFCBFD382736FD2CFDD4" box="[713,763,547,573]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">type</typeStatus>
locality)
</materialsCitation>
; however, more recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF80CCC72277FFCBFB7E2736FAA3FDD4" author="Rheinheimer, J." box="[1167,1396,547,573]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" pagination="59 - 72" refId="ref29953" refString="Rheinheimer, J. (2010) Les Hylobiini de Guyane (Coleoptera, Curculionidae). Coleopteres de Guyane, 1, 59 - 72." type="journal article" year="2010">Rheinheimer (2010)</bibRefCitation>
recorded it in 
<collectingCountry id="F306F1A62277FFCBFEEF2752FE10FD88" box="[286,455,583,609]" name="French Guiana" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAEB1362277FFCBFF36277FFDCCFD6C" blockId="23.[151,1437,151,645]" box="[199,539,618,645]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="B9656D242277FFCBFF36277FFE49FD6C" bold="true" box="[199,414,618,645]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Associated plants.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
